<h1><span id="Sicilian_Defence.2C_Najdorf_Variation"></span><span id="Sicilian_Defence,_Najdorf_Variation">Sicilian Defence, Najdorf Variation</span></h1>
<p>Moves:1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6.Be3
</p><p>In recent years, the most popular way for white to combat the Najdorf Variation at master level has been 6.Be3. A flexible opening, it has been employed successfully by Grandmasters such as Robert Byrne, Nigel Short &amp; John Nunn.
